{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0c6541c-5e9e-4c3f-864d-8b29fc3d70bc","content":"With xUnit v3 + MTP, the VSTest filter syntax changes. Here's the translation:\n\n**Old (VSTest / xUnit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP / xUnit v3):**\n```\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nWait — actually the key difference is simpler than that. With MTP enabled (`UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`), `dotnet test --filter` still works but the **filter syntax** changes:\n\n**Translated command:**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Trait=Category%3DSmoke\"\n```\n\nOr using the MTP native `--treenode-filter` (passed after `--`):\n\n```\ndotnet test -- --filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n\n| Concept | VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---------|-------------|----------|\n| AND operator | `&` | `and` (or `&`) |\n| Trait filter | `Category=Smoke` | `Trait=Category%3DSmoke` |\n| Native filter | N/A | `--treenode-filter` glob syntax |\n\nThe critical breaking change is **trait filtering**. In MTP, traits are expressed as `Trait=Key%3DValue` (URL-encoded `=`) rather than `Key=Value` directly.\n\n**Recommended CI command:**\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Trait=Category%3DSmoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"64a2ef46-5589-4d9d-ad46-e72e5c5d7024","outputTokens":427,"requestId":"BC2F:214B1C:1B6DF89:1E85B8D:69FA90FC"},"id":"54c6ecae-bd7c-443f-a2e2-86f2ac4a8c89","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:53:28.348Z","parentId":"56fd16b3-be09-4d26-8fa4-a76c55a05b95"}
